The Speed Wing installation tool is designed with “wings” to enable the installer to reach tight areas typically out of the reach of most bump, bondo, teflon and hard cards. The Speed Wing also comes with a unique feature of having one flat edge and one curved edge. The curved edge is designed with proprietary Control Contour Technology (CCT) which enables the tool to encourage a finger or bubble to disperse outward which reduces the chances of a crease. Finally, the Speed Wing material is made from a unique blend of materials that enable it to slide across most film surfaces easily while still maintaining the rigidity lay the material flat and remove any moisture or air trapped underneath. We offer the Speedwing in 3 different colors, each color offers a difference in flexibility. The Red is the softest, the Green is in the middle, and the Yellow is the hardest. Try the Speed Wing today and add a Solskin Wet edge strip and/or Solskin telfon tape for additional application needs. Available in 4", 6", and 8".

The AP1 Square Corner Blue Hard Card is the softest and most flexible. This extremely flexible card is ideal for laying down the Dot-Matrix area. The flexibility allows the user to gently purge the glue out without removing too much. This card is also popular for Paint Protection Film installations. The AP1 cards have  a texture  that is slightly easier to grip with wet, soapy hands and are now available in a new design which incorporates one squared corner. This new improved design makes it easier to get into tight corners when bumping edges dry and when trimming film.  Made in the USA

The Speed Wing installation tool is designed with “wings” to enable the installer to reach tight areas typically out of the reach of most bump, bondo, teflon and hard cards. The Speed Wing also comes with a unique feature of having one flat edge and one curved edge. The curved edge is designed with proprietary Control Contour Technology (CCT) which enables the tool to encourage a finger or bubble to disperse outward which reduces the chances of a crease. Finally, the Speed Wing material is made from a unique blend of materials that enable it to slide across most film surfaces easily while still maintaining the rigidity lay the material flat and remove any moisture or air trapped underneath. We offer the Speed Wing in 3 different colors, each color offers a difference in flexibility. The Red is the softest, the Green is in the middle, and the Yellow is the hardest! Try the Speed Wing today and add a Solskin Wet edge strip and/or Solskin telfon tape for additional application needs. Available in 4", 6", and 8".

The new Speed Wing with Suede Blade Edge. Not only does this tool feature the “Wings” at the tips to enable it to get into tighter spaces, it also features the Pro Tool Now Control Contour Technology (CCT) on the non-suede edge. However, the real feature than takes this tool over the top is the All NEW, Pro Tool Now exclusive, Suede Blade Edge. Like other suede, felt or teflon edges on the market today, the Suede Blade has the precise amount of flex and give where you want it combined with the rigidity when you need it. Best of all, it glides over window tint, paint protection film and vinyl graphics/wraps with an ease that will leave you astounded. Innovative new product from ProTools Now has a soft and flexible covering with a dual layer suede surface to give you serious flexibility when carding. Red Suede Blade is softer/more flexible than the Yellow Suede Blade

Made to reduce the problem of scratching gloss and chrome vinyl during wet applications. 4" Solskin Wet Strips (10 pack) are excellent for soaking up water during wet application and you have the freedom to choose your favorite squeegee to apply the product when needed rather than replacing the entire squeegee. We have also tested this product on turbo squeegee's during PPF installation and have received great results.

4" Monkey Strips (10 pack) are awesome for installing vinyl during dry application. Apply Monkey Strips to your favorite squeegee and work closer to the vinyl and hard to reach areas during installation because of the thin design.

Place PTFE Coated Glass Fabric Tape w/Liner (1" X 3') on your favorite squeegee during installation and heat shrinking. This tape slides across film with ease and is Heat Resistant up to 350 degrees (180c).  PTFE Coated Glass Fabric Tape w/Liner also has properties to reduce static and was developed by an installer. This tape is intended to be used on hard cards and bondo style cards. Not intended for use on Blue Max or squeegees.
